<subSubSection id="5FF065107D17FFEF65ADFAD6FF22AAE8" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="1755369B7D17FFEF65ADFAD6FF22AAE8" blockId="8.[151,1438,869,1721]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="259EEA897D17FFEF65ADFAD6FE7EA97C" bold="true" box="[199,399,1301,1326]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis id="259EEA897D17FFEF65ADFAD6FEB0A97C" box="[199,321,1301,1326]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" reason="1">
<emphasis id="259EEA897D17FFEF65ADFAD6FECBA97F" bold="true" box="[199,314,1301,1326]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Male:
</emphasis>
Easy to recognize by mostly black dorsum of thorax (Fig. 34B—shared with 
<taxonomicName id="D0EA4D187D17FFEF6066FAD5FA6AA97C" authorityName="Costa &amp; Santos" authorityYear="2000" box="[1292,1435,1302,1325]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="muryense">
<emphasis id="259EEA897D17FFEF6066FAD5FA6AA97C" box="[1292,1435,1302,1325]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">H. muryense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D0EA4D187D17FFEF65A1FAF9FE8DA900" authorityName="Machado &amp; Bede" authorityYear="2006" box="[203,380,1337,1361]" class="Insecta" family="Megapodagrionidae" genus="Heteragrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tiradentense">
<emphasis id="259EEA897D17FFEF65A1FAF9FE8DA900" box="[203,380,1337,1361]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">H. tiradentense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
—but these two species have the mesepisternum interrupted by a pale spot) and strongly swollen base of cercus occupying 2/3 of its length (Fig. 15B). Cercus in lateral view: dorsobasal expansion present. Ventrobasal expansion very large, occupying 2/3 length, its ventral margin almost straight (Fig. 15B). Cercus in mediodorsal view: Basal, medial and apical portions of cercus subequal. Ventral expansion present and sparsely hairy. Ventral branch of medial process rectangular plate with apical end rounded, dorsal branch roughly triangular and fused with ventral branch on its inner side (Fig. 15A). 
<emphasis id="259EEA897D17FFEF665CFA2EFC7CAA54" bold="true" box="[822,909,1517,1541]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Female</emphasis>
: Posterior lobe of prothorax semicircular with small notch in middle, pale yellow with large ovoid black spot in middle bordered with brown and tips covered with short hairs (Fig. 46C); valves of ovipositor reaching but not surpassing distal S10 and in lateral view ventral margin with small spines (
<figureCitation id="8FD12A1E7D17FFEF64D1F99AFDD1AA20" box="[443,544,1625,1649]" captionStart="FIGURE 48" captionStartId="59.[151,250,1473,1496]" captionTargetBox="[405,1165,197,1445]" captionTargetId="figure-45@59.[392,1194,193,1453]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURE 48. Female: Heteragrion muryense (A) S8–S10, (B) basal plate; Heteragrion tiradentense (allotype) (C) S8–S10, (D) basal plate; Heteragrion flavovittatum (E) S8–S10, (F) basal plate; Heteragrion ictericum (G) S8–S10, (H) basal plate." pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 48E</figureCitation>
); Cercus subequal to S10, apparently without bristles at the tip (
<figureCitation id="8FD12A1E7D17FFEF618FF99AFABBAA20" box="[1253,1354,1625,1649]" captionStart="FIGURE 48" captionStartId="59.[151,250,1473,1496]" captionTargetBox="[405,1165,197,1445]" captionTargetId="figure-45@59.[392,1194,193,1453]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURE 48. Female: Heteragrion muryense (A) S8–S10, (B) basal plate; Heteragrion tiradentense (allotype) (C) S8–S10, (D) basal plate; Heteragrion flavovittatum (E) S8–S10, (F) basal plate; Heteragrion ictericum (G) S8–S10, (H) basal plate." pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 48E</figureCitation>
); Basal plate: dorsal edge an inverted S-shape, longer than convex outer edge. Ventral side 2/3 length of outer edge (
<figureCitation id="8FD12A1E7D17FFEF6005F9BEFF37AAE8" captionStart="FIGURE 48" captionStartId="59.[151,250,1473,1496]" captionTargetBox="[405,1165,197,1445]" captionTargetId="figure-45@59.[392,1194,193,1453]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURE 48. Female: Heteragrion muryense (A) S8–S10, (B) basal plate; Heteragrion tiradentense (allotype) (C) S8–S10, (D) basal plate; Heteragrion flavovittatum (E) S8–S10, (F) basal plate; Heteragrion ictericum (G) S8–S10, (H) basal plate." pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 48F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
